    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped pepper</strong>, <strong>courgette</strong> <strong>chunks</strong> and<strong> red onion wedges</strong> to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] on the bottom shelf of the oven and cook for 30 min or until golden and cooked through – this is your <strong>roasted veg</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1639392231595-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1639392231595-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1639392231595-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1639392231595-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1639392231595-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, crush your <strong>garlic cloves</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife and remove the skins</p><p>Add the<strong> crushed garlic </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the dish with the<strong> </strong>chicken<strong> </strong>and cook for 30 secs</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1639392235465-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1639392235465-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1639392235465-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1639392235465-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1639392235465-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Sprinkle in your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong>, then add your<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong>, <strong>dried basil</strong> and 450ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[600ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[750ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Stir through your<strong> tortiglioni</strong></p><p>Tip: Nestle as much of the pasta as you can into the sauce to help it cook evenly!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1639392238493-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1639392238493-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1639392238493-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1639392238493-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1639392238493-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for 25-30 min or until the pasta and chicken are cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p><p>Tip: Give the pasta a stir and roasted veg a mix after 15 min</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1639392241780-x200.jpg",
